  +### UC-5 IMPLEMENTATION RESULT (mc-r1-dmc-abort-timing) — KEY FINDING: the `01x16` is NOT an abort
  +Ported the TriCNES implicit-DMA-abort ARMING model faithfully under `mc-r1-dmc-abort-timing`
  +(default-off; floor + flag-on both 9 fails / 93.53%, nestest 0-diff, fmt/clippy clean):
  +- `arm_dmc_implicit_abort_on_enable` latches `set_implicit_abort` only on a `$4015` ENABLE landing at
  +  the TriCNES timer phase (`dmc_cycles_until_output == 10` on get / `== 8` on put; Emulator.cs 9542),
  +  with a DISABLE-write clear so a looping-enable latch cannot leak into the next sample's load.
  +- `complete_dmc_dma{,_before_get_tick}` raise the 1-cycle abort ONLY when that latch is set (consuming
  +  it), instead of the floor's unconditional "any 1-byte non-loop load completed" arm.
  +- The disable-triggered EXPLICIT abort is narrowed to TriCNES `cuo==2 && get` (vs the floor `cuo in
  +  {1,2,3}`); the get-only-1-halt / put-cancel access path (`read1`/`write1`) is reused from
  +  `mc-r1-dmc-abort-cancel`.
  +
  +**DECISIVE EXPERIMENT (refutes the UC-5 "abort behavior is the make-or-break" premise).** A diagnostic
  +that NUKES every abort source every CPU cycle (`pending_dmc_abort = dmc_abort_delay = set_implicit_abort
  += 0`) leaves the implicit `$500` sweep **byte-identical at `01x16`**. Independently, suppressing the
  +1-byte load DMA also leaves it `01x16`. Therefore the implicit `01x16` over-fire is **a real DMC LOAD/
  +RELOAD DMA landing inside CalculateDMADuration's measurement window at every sweep offset — the DMC-DMA
  +ABSOLUTE-LANDING-CYCLE incoherence (the R-1 / master-clock axis) — NOT abort servicing.** Key1 wants
  +`00` at idx 0-9,12-15 because at those offsets TriCNES's DMA lands OUTSIDE the window; RustyNES's lands
  +inside at every offset. This matches the prior R-1 memo ("01x16 vs Key1 ... = the DMC-DMA absolute-
  +landing-cycle incoherence (NOT abort servicing)") and means no flag-gated abort change can move these
  +three tests; the lever is the absolute landing-cycle coherence (multi-week master-clock work). The
